73-74. Titio: the identityof this man and the reason for his presence here have been much discussed. One important reason for his appearance is to form a transition to 3 topics traditionally associated with this theme, viz. the situation iu 74, the magister amoris, 77-80, and physician, heul thyself, 81-84. Otherwise the elegy would not only end tamely at 72 but it would also he incomplete. Another and in itself asufficient reason for Titius here was as we shall see to mislead the reader for the time being.
